40|$|Since 1998, TNO Defence, Security and Safety has {{performed}} operational analysis with the Underwater Warfare Testbed, which provides an environment for evaluation and validation of systems, concepts, and tactics. On {{top of this}} testbed the <b>Torpedo</b> <b>Defence</b> System TestBed has been built to simulate torpedoes, torpedo detection systems and torpedo countermeasures. Studies are performed in a research programme in which knowledge in this field is acquired to support the Royal Netherlands Navy in the procurement of new <b>torpedoes</b> and <b>torpedo</b> <b>defence</b> systems. This paper focuses on the most recent studies into the use of existing sonar systems (towed, hull mounted and dipping) to detect torpedoes. The detection performance results {{are used in the}} Area <b>Torpedo</b> <b>Defence</b> study to determine the composition of ship formations, which are in transit or operate in expeditionary operations including sea basing. Furthermore, the deployment of torpedo countermeasures in two different <b>torpedo</b> <b>defence</b> concepts is investigated...|$|R
